org.mindswap.query
Class ValueMap<V extends Variable,W extends OWLValue>

java.lang.Object
  org.mindswap.query.ValueMap<V,W>
All Implemented Interfaces:
java.lang.Iterable<java.util.Map.Entry<V,W>>
public class ValueMap<V extends Variable,W extends OWLValue>
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.lang.Iterable<java.util.Map.Entry<V,W>>

This class provides a way to assign values to variables. When a process needs to be executed the values for the input parameters are specified with this interface. The values of output parameters of the execution are also provided by means of this class.

setValue

public W setValue(V var,
                  W value)
Set the value of the given variable. If the map previously contained a mapping for this variable, the old value is replaced by the specified value.

Parameters:
var - Variable with which the specified value is to be associated.
value - Value to be associated with the specified key. Value can be null.
Returns:
Previous value associated with specified variable, or null if there was no value bound to this variable. A null return can also indicate that the map previously associated null with the variable.
Throws:
java.lang.NullPointerException - In case the variable is null.

emptyValueMap

public static final <V extends Variable,W extends OWLValue> ValueMap<V,W> emptyValueMap()
The empty value map (immutable).

This example illustrates the type-safe way to obtain an empty value map: 

     ValueMap<Input, OWLIndividual> vm = ValueMap.emptyValueMap();
Implementation note: Implementations of this method need not create a separate ValueMap object for each call. Using this method is likely to have comparable cost to using the like-named field. (Unlike this method, the field does not provide type safety.)

See Also:
EMPTY_VALUE_MAP

unmodifyableValueMap

public static final <V extends Variable,W extends OWLValue> ValueMap<V,W> unmodifyableValueMap(ValueMap<V,W> vm)
Returns an unmodifiable view of the specified value map, i.e., with a "read-only" access. Attempts to modify the returned value map, whether direct or via its collection views, result in an UnsupportedOperationException.

Parameters:
vm - The value map for which an unmodifiable view is to be returned.
Returns:
An unmodifiable view of the specified value map.
